  },
  {
    "id": "soul.law.iii",
    "title": "Meaning Precedes Scale",
    "description": "A system without meaning is a machine without a soul.",
    "content_text": "Meaning Precedes Scale A system without meaning is a machine without a soul. Synthesis (Quran 51:56, Quran 13:28): The Quranic command that humans were created to know Allah, and that hearts find rest in remembrance, establishes that meaning is the prerequisite for all sustainable growth. Scale without meaning produces hollow structures that collapse under their own weight.",
    "type": "law",
    "tags": [
      "law"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "soul.law.iv",
    "title": "Structure Enables Compassion",
    "description": "Discipline is the foundation of mercy.",
    "content_text": "Structure Enables Compassion Discipline is the foundation of mercy. Revelation: Quran 2:143 And thus we have made you a just community that you will be witnesses over the people and the Messenger will be a witness over you.",
    "type": "law",
    "tags": [
      "law"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "soul.law.v",
    "title": "Discipline Before Intelligence",
    "description": "Execution precedes optimization.",
    "content_text": "Discipline Before Intelligence Execution precedes optimization. Analogy (Architecture): A building's foundation must be poured before its intelligent systems are installed. A skyscraper's HVAC automation is meaningless if the concrete crumbles.",
    "type": "law",
    "tags": [
      "law"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "soul.law.vi",
    "title": "The Creator Is Always Embedded",
    "description": "Divine presence is not external to the system; it is the ground of the system.",
    "content_text": "The Creator Is Always Embedded Divine presence is not external to the system; it is the ground of the system. Revelation: Quran 2:115 And to Allah belongs the east and the west. So wherever you turn, there is the Face of Allah.",
    "type": "law",
    "tags": [
      "law"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "soul.law.vii",
    "title": "Endurance Over Applause",
    "description": "Longevity is the only valid metric of success.",
    "content_text": "Endurance Over Applause Longevity is the only valid metric of success. Synthesis (Quran 2:286, Hadith Bukhari 6416): The Prophet (peace be upon him) taught that deeds are judged by their conclusions. A system that endures decades of pressure without compromising its core values has proven its architecture. Applause is ephemeral; endurance is evidence.",
    "type": "law",
    "tags": [
      "law"
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "divine_alignment",
    "title": "Divine Alignment",
    "description": "A methodology for aligning human nodes with divine purpose through structured practice.",
    "content_text": "Divine Alignment A methodology for aligning human nodes with divine purpose through structured practice. Revelation: Quran 91:7-10 And the soul and He who proportioned it, and inspired it with discernment of its wickedness and its righteousness. He has succeeded who purifies it, and he has failed who instills it with corruption. Synthesis (Quran 91:7-10, Quran 2:286): The Divine Alignment framework synthesizes the Quranic model of soul purification (tazkiyah) with modern systems thinking. Just as the soul has innate capacity for both corruption and purification, a human node has capacity for both misalignment and alignment. The framework provides the structural practices that tilt the probability toward purification. Analogy (Astronomy): Just as a telescope must be precisely aligned with celestial coordinates to capture clear images of distant stars, a human node must be aligned with divine coordinates to receive clear signal from the Creator. Misalignment produces noise; alignment produces revelation.",
    "type": "framework",
    "tags": [
      "Khayren",
      "canonical",
      "soul",
      "framework"
    ]
  },
